{"GUID":"d16cef6d-5e48-418d-aaa2-e7ced172277d","Type":"Text","Text":"Joel Christner 1264 N Monroe St, San Jose, CA 95128 | (408) 396-3007 joel.christner@gmail.com | www.joelchristner.com | github @jchristn OBJECTIVE Experienced technologist and developer seeking business challenges that require elegant, powerful solutions to establish new markets or disrupt existing markets. EXPERIENCE 5/2017 – Present CloudGenix, Inc. www.cloudgenix.com Vice President, Marketing San Jose, CA Responsible for overarching brand, visual, and product identity. Transformed the business successfully from technology evangelization to sales enablement. Responsible for all content, graphics, web presence, social, campaigns, and budget. Designed and implemented developer ecosystem including SDKs, documentation, and partner empowerment to grow managed services business. 12/2014 – 5/2017 Cake, Corp. (acq by Sysco Foods) www.trycake.com Chief Architect, Payments Platform Redwood City, CA Designed and built credit, debit, and ACH payments platform with capacity to scale to hundreds of billions of dollars in annual payment volume. Managed existing payments infrastructure through 10X growth over two year period. 12/2011 – 12/2014 Cube, Co. (acq by Rocket Lawyer) www.getcube.com Co-founder, Chief Technology Officer Mountain View, CA Built a payments company and API banking platform, grew to thousands of merchants, dozens of developer partners, and hundreds of millions in credit card and ACH volume prior to sale. Built developer ecosystem including SDKs, documentation, and onboarding. 8/2009 – 12/2011 StorSimple, Inc. (acq by Microsoft) www.storsimple.com Distinguished Engineer, Chief Scientist Santa Clara, CA System and solution architecture and design, all aspects of product management and technical marketing. Led company to market leadership position with key analysts. Helped grow to first hundred customers while establishing several references and beachheads. 8/2008 – 8/2009 Cisco Systems, Inc. www.cisco.com Technical Leader San Jose, CA Company-wide solution architecture for application delivery and application performance management strategy, system architecture for Wide Area Application Services (WAAS) product line. 7/2007 – 8/2008 Reconnex Corporation (acq by McAfee) www.reconnex.net Director, Product Management Mountain View, CA Established product line strategy and architecture for data loss prevention family of products. Led to Gartner and Forrester recognition as market leader. Increased revenue 50% QoQ and over 200% YoY, and competitive win rate from 50% to 80%. 12/2002 – 7/2007 Cisco Systems, Inc. www.cisco.com Sr Manager, Technical Marketing, Application Delivery San Jose, CA Systems Engineer, Storage Networking Englewood, CO 6/1998 – 12/2002 Employed by two Midwest consulting firms focusing on data center, storage, and networking
AREAS OF EXPERTISE Full stack and cross-platform software development on multiple platforms (Windows, Mac, Linux) and mobile. Proficient in C#, Java, Javascript. Understanding and experience with Python, PHP, Objective-C. Focus areas are API platforms, distributed systems, networking, databases, data storage, messaging, information search and retrieval, deduplication, and cloud infrastructure.
PUBLICATIONS nd 2009 Deploying Cisco Wide Area Application Services 2 Edition (Book, 600pp, Cisco Press) 2008 Deploying Cisco Wide Area Application Services (Book, 400pp, Cisco Press) 2007 Application Acceleration and WAN Optimization Fundamentals (Book, 400pp, Cisco Press) 2006 Contributor to Storage Networking Protocol Fundamentals (Book, 500pp, Cisco Press)
EDUCATION 1/2007 – 7/2010 Columbia University, MS Computer Science www.columbia.edu New York City, NY 6/1995 – 6/1998 DeVry University, BS Electronics Engineering www.dpg.devry.edu Addison, IL
PAST CERTIFICATIONS Chose not to renew the following previously-held certifications: - Cisco Certified Internetwork Expert #15311 – Data Center and Storage - Cisco Certified Network Professional, Design Professional, and Network Associate - Microsoft Certified Systems Engineer - Brocade Certified Fabric Professional and SAN Designer
OPEN SOURCE CONTRIBUTIONS Numerous open source projects released on Github and various package managers under the MIT license. Some of these packages have had tens of thousands of installations. - WatsonWebserver – High performance async programmable RESTful web server - WatsonMesh – Simple mesh networking library with integrated framing, reliable delivery, and events - WatsonDedupe – Self-contained deduplication with external chunk storage and scalability - WatsonCluster – Cluster state and communications library for 1+1 high availability applications - WatsonTcp – TCP client, server with framing, reliable delivery, and simple integration for RPC applications - Komodo – Information search and retrieval platform with APIs, elastic scalability, and externalized storage - Kvpbase – Elastic, scalable, RESTful object storage platform and SDKs - BigQ – Message queue with support for pub-sub, channels, unicast, broadcast, mcast
